#. <section class="sutta" id="sn3.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Kosala"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 24. Issattasutta → issatthasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Issattasutta"
msgstr "24. Archery"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.99"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.220"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, King Pasenadi said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.3"
msgid "“kattha nu kho, bhante, dānaṃ dātabban”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, where should a gift be given?”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.4"
msgid "“Yattha kho, mahārāja, cittaṃ pasīdatī”ti."
msgstr "“Wherever your heart feels inspired, great king.”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.5"
msgid "“Kattha pana, bhante, dinnaṃ mahapphalan”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, where is a gift very fruitful?”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.6"
msgid ""
"“Aññaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, kattha dānaṃ dātabbaṃ, aññaṃ panetaṃ kattha "
"dinnaṃ mahapphalanti?"
msgstr ""
"“Where a gift should be given is one thing, great king, but where a gift is "
"very fruitful is another."

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.7"
msgid "Sīlavato kho, mahārāja, dinnaṃ mahapphalaṃ, no tathā dussīle."
msgstr ""
"A gift is very fruitful when it’s given to an ethical person, not so much to "
"an unethical person."

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.8"
msgid ""
"Tena hi, mahārāja, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā, te khameyya, tathā "
"naṃ byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"Well then, great king, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer "
"as you like."

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.9"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "What do you think, great king? "

#. VAR: samupabyūḷho → samūpabbūḷho (bj, pts2) | samupabbuḷho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.10"
msgid "idha tyassa yuddhaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ saṅgāmo samupabyūḷho."
msgstr "Suppose you were at war, ready to fight a battle."

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.11"
msgid ""
"Atha āgaccheyya khattiyakumāro asikkhito akatahattho akatayoggo akatūpāsano "
"bhīru chambhī utrāsī palāyī."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes an aristocrat youth who is untrained, inexpert, unfit, "
"inexperienced. And he’s fearful, cowardly, trembling, quick to flee."

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.12"
msgid "Bhareyyāsi taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca te tādisena purisenā”ti?"
msgstr "Would you employ such a man? Would he be of any use to you?”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.13"
msgid ""
"“Nāhaṃ, bhante, bhareyyaṃ taṃ purisaṃ, na ca me attho tādisena purisenā”ti."
msgstr "“No, sir, I would have no use for such a man.”"

# Note that, while the khattiyas were often said to be the warrior class, there is no difference here.
msgctxt "sn3.24:1.14"
msgid "“Atha āgaccheyya brāhmaṇakumāro asikkhito … pe …"
msgstr "“What about a brahmin youth,"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.15"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya vessakumāro asikkhito … pe …"
msgstr "a merchant youth,"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.16"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya suddakumāro asikkhito … pe …"
msgstr "or a worker youth who was similar?”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:1.17"
msgid "na ca me attho tādisena purisenā”ti."
msgstr "“No, sir, I would have no use for such a man.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.222"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, mahārāja, "
msgstr "“What do you think, great king? "

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.2"
msgid "idha tyassa yuddhaṃ paccupaṭṭhitaṃ saṅgāmo samupabyūḷho."
msgstr "Suppose you were at war, ready to fight a battle."

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.3"
msgid ""
"Atha āgaccheyya khattiyakumāro susikkhito katahattho katayoggo katūpāsano "
"abhīru acchambhī anutrāsī apalāyī."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes an aristocrat youth who is trained, expert, fit, "
"experienced. And he’s fearless, brave, bold, standing his ground."

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.4"
msgid "Bhareyyāsi taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca te tādisena purisenā”ti?"
msgstr "Would you employ such a man? Would he be of any use to you?”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.5"
msgid "“Bhareyyāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca me tādisena purisenā”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, sir, I would have a use for such a man.”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.6"
msgid "“Atha āgaccheyya brāhmaṇakumāro … pe …"
msgstr "“What about a brahmin youth,"

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.7"
msgid "atha āgaccheyya vessakumāro … pe …"
msgstr "a merchant youth,"

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.8"
msgid ""
"atha āgaccheyya suddakumāro susikkhito katahattho katayoggo katūpāsano "
"abhīru acchambhī anutrāsī apalāyī."
msgstr "or a worker youth who was similar?"

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.9"
msgid "Bhareyyāsi taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca te tādisena purisenā”ti?"
msgstr "Would you employ such a man? Would he be of any use to you?”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:2.10"
msgid "“Bhareyyāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ purisaṃ, attho ca me tādisena purisenā”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, sir, I would have a use for such a man.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.100"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.223"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: yasmā kasmā cepi → yasmā cepi (si, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn3.24:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, mahārāja, yasmā kasmā cepi kulā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito "
"hoti, so ca hoti pañcaṅgavippahīno pañcaṅgasamannāgato, tasmiṃ dinnaṃ "
"mahapphalaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, a gift to anyone who has given up five factors and "
"possesses five factors is very fruitful, no matter what family they’ve gone "
"forth from."

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañcaṅgāni pahīnāni honti?"
msgstr "What are the five factors they’ve given up?"

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.3"
msgid ""
"Kāmacchando pahīno hoti, byāpādo pahīno hoti, thinamiddhaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, "
"uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahīnaṃ hoti, vicikicchā pahīnā hoti."
msgstr ""
"Sensual desire, ill will, dullness and drowsiness, restlessness and remorse, "
"and doubt."

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.4"
msgid "Imāni pañcaṅgāni pahīnāni honti."
msgstr "These are the five factors they’ve given up."

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.5"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato hoti?"
msgstr "What are the five factors they possess?"

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.6"
msgid ""
"Asekkhena sīlakkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena samādhikkhandhena "
"samannāgato hoti, asekkhena paññākkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena "
"vimuttikkhandhena samannāgato hoti, asekkhena vimuttiñāṇadassanakkhandhena "
"samannāgato hoti."
msgstr ""
"The entire spectrum of an adept’s ethics, immersion, wisdom, freedom, and "
"knowledge and vision of freedom."

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.7"
msgid "Imehi pañcahaṅgehi samannāgato hoti."
msgstr "These are the five factors they possess."

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.8"
msgid "Iti pañcaṅgavippahīne pañcaṅgasamannāgate dinnaṃ mahapphalan”ti."
msgstr ""
"I say that a gift to anyone who has given up these five factors and "
"possesses these five factors is very fruitful.”"

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.9"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn3.24:3.10"
msgid "satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: Issattaṃ → issatthaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
#. VAR: balavīriyañca → balaviriyañca (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.1"
msgid "“Issattaṃ balavīriyañca,"
msgstr "“Any youth skilled at archery,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.2"
msgid "yasmiṃ vijjetha māṇave;"
msgstr "powerful and vigorous,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ yuddhattho bhare rājā,"
msgstr "would be employed by a king going to war—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:4.4"
msgid "nāsūraṃ jātipaccayā."
msgstr "one is not a coward because of one’s birth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.1"
msgid "Tatheva khantisoraccaṃ,"
msgstr "Just so, whoever is settled"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.2"
msgid "dhammā yasmiṃ patiṭṭhitā;"
msgstr "in the qualities of patience and gentleness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.3"
msgid "Ariyavuttiṃ medhāviṃ,"
msgstr "a clever person with noble conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:5.4"
msgid "hīnajaccampi pūjaye."
msgstr "should be venerated even if they’re low born."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.1"
msgid "Kāraye assame ramme,"
msgstr "You should build lovely hermitages"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.2"
msgid "vāsayettha bahussute;"
msgstr "and settle learned people in them."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.3"
msgid "Papañca vivane kayirā,"
msgstr "You should set up water supplies in barren regions"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:6.4"
msgid "dugge saṅkamanāni ca."
msgstr "and passages in places hard to travel."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.224"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.1"
msgid "Annaṃ pānaṃ khādanīyaṃ,"
msgstr "Food, drink, edibles,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.2"
msgid "vatthasenāsanāni ca;"
msgstr "clothes, and lodgings"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.3"
msgid "Dadeyya ujubhūtesu,"
msgstr "should be given to the upright ones,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:7.4"
msgid "vippasannena cetasā."
msgstr "with a clear and confident heart."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.1"
msgid "Yathā hi megho thanayaṃ,"
msgstr "The thundering rain cloud,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.2"
msgid "vijjumālī satakkaku;"
msgstr "its hundred peaks wreathed in lightning,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.3"
msgid "Thalaṃ ninnañca pūreti,"
msgstr "pours down over the rich earth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:8.4"
msgid "abhivassaṃ vasundharaṃ."
msgstr "soaking the uplands and valleys."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.1"
msgid "Tatheva saddho sutavā,"
msgstr "So too an astute person,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.2"
msgid "abhisaṅkhacca bhojanaṃ;"
msgstr "faithful and learned,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.3"
msgid "Vanibbake tappayati,"
msgstr "should prepare a meal to satisfy"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:9.4"
msgid "annapānena paṇḍito."
msgstr "renunciates with food and drink."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.1"
msgid "Āmodamāno pakireti,"
msgstr "Rejoicing, they distribute,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.2"
msgid "detha dethāti bhāsati;"
msgstr "saying, ‘Give! give!’"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.3"
msgid "Taṃ hissa gajjitaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "For that is their thunder,"

# The Upanishads say that the thunder is the roar of Brahma. Thus it seems that, while the animist heritage of deva=sky is usually backgrounded, here it is rather more specific.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.4"
msgid "devasseva pavassato;"
msgstr "like the gods when it rains."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.5"
msgid "Sā puññadhārā vipulā,"
msgstr "That stream of merit so abundant"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn3.24:10.6"
msgid "dātāraṃ abhivassatī”ti."
msgstr "showers down on the giver.”"
